  "time_ut": 1660647448,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db4\u0d82\u0da0\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dda\u0daf\u0dd3 \u0db4\u0ddc\u0dbd\u0dd2\u0dc3\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc4\u0db1\u0dc0\u0dbd\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dc4\u0dbb \u0daf\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca \u0dad\u0dc0\u0dad\u0dca \u0d85\u0dba\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d85\u0dbd\u0dca\u0dbd\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Another person who attacked police vehicles in Panchikawatta is arrested",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "A 31-year-old youth was charged with assaulting DIG TP Gamlath and Superintendent of Police Nalaka Senanayake in Maradana Panchikawatta area last May (9) and setting fire to the cars they were traveling in and stealing the duty firearm from the Superintendent of Police. Police said that the arrest was made by the Criminal Investigation Department.",
        "The arrested suspect is a resident of Maligawatta Laksetha Sevana apartment complex.",
        "The commercial crime investigation section of the Criminal Investigation Department has started investigations into this incident and arrested the suspect.",
        "A group including this suspect attacked the drivers of the police constables who drove their official vehicles to the Deputy Inspector General of Police and the Superintendent of Police who were traveling on the road at Panchikawatta Mansandhi on May 9, kidnapped the vehicles and took their spare parts and set fire to the vehicles. The police said that they have participated.",
        "It also says that the Public Property Act deals with laws under the Penal Code and the Firearms Ordinance.",
        "Previously, two suspects were arrested in connection with this incident and a part of the Superintendent of Police's official car was found in the custody of one of the suspects."
      ],
